{
  "name": "20260414-001-jm-simple-3tp-legacy",
  "description": "Legacy JM Simple 3TP ported into the composable framework. Parity gate for chunk 8 — the runtime + block composition must reproduce the old hardcoded engine's metrics (PF, net, maxDD, trade list) to within a tight tolerance before we deprecate engine/strategy.js. Notes: (a) atrLen and stochLen appear in two blocks each (hardStop+target; entry+trail); cross-block equality constraints aren't yet expressible, so the parity smoke test pins identical values by hand. (b) atrScaleOutTarget supports up to 6 tranches; this legacy port uses 3. Tranches 4-6 are disabled by pinning tpNPct=0, which drops them from the genome AND stops the runtime from creating subs for them. (c) tp3Pct is an explicit GA-optimized share under the generic block (legacy made it implicit as the remainder); runtime normalizes tp1Pct+tp2Pct+tp3Pct to 100% automatically, so the sum-constraint problem from before doesn't apply. Both alias support and sum constraints are tracked in backlog.",
